The House of Copier (Coppier, Coupier or Couppier) is a noble family from Savoy. The family is represented by the Association d'Entraide pour la Noblesse (ANF), the French Mutual Aid Association for Nobility. It is one of the oldest European families and is recognized of French and Dutch nobility. This family of landowners illustrated itself in industry, science and in the judiciary system. It also gave many religious figures to France.
